{
  "page": "Khalasar",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:T_Jedruszek_drogo_khalasar.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/87/T_Jedruszek_drogo_khalasar.jpg/400px-T_Jedruszek_drogo_khalasar.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"329\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/87/T_Jedruszek_drogo_khalasar.jpg/600px-T_Jedruszek_drogo_khalasar.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/87/T_Jedruszek_drogo_khalasar.jpg/800px-T_Jedruszek_drogo_khalasar.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:T_Jedruszek_drogo_khalasar.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Drogo's enormous khalasar - by Tomasz Jedruszek. © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>A <i><b>khalasar</b></i> is a nomadic horde of <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki\" title=\"Dothraki\">Dothraki</a> led by a chief called a <i><a href=\"/index.php/Khal\" title=\"Khal\">khal</a></i>. The heir to a <i>khalasar</i> is the <i>khal's</i> son, the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Khalakka\" title=\"Khalakka\">khalakka</a></i>.  \n</p><p><i>Khalasars</i> come in various sizes; the more powerful and feared the <i>khal</i>, the larger his <i>khalasar</i>. Before the age of thirty Khal <a href=\"/index.php/Drogo\" title=\"Drogo\">Drogo</a> led an enormous <i>khalasar</i> forty thousand strong.\n</p><p><i>Khalasars</i> are broken into groups, called <i><a href=\"/index.php/Khas\" title=\"Khas\">khas</a></i>, which are each led by one of the <i>khal's</i> captains, called <i><a href=\"/index.php/Ko\" title=\"Ko\">kos</a></i>. When a <i>khal</i> dies or becomes too weak to lead, a new <i>khal</i> may take control of the <i>khalasar</i> or the <i>khas</i> may break away and form new <i>khalasars</i> led by their former <i>kos</i>. \n</p><p>The Dothraki will not follow a child <i>khalakka</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Instead, the <i>kos</i> will fight among themselves to take the place of the fallen <i>khal</i> and the <i>khalakka</i> will be killed so that he does not grow up to become a rival.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Khalasar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Death rides with every khalasar. <sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Fall upon one of these khalasars and destroy it, and you may find that the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki\" title=\"Dothraki\">Dothraki</a> are not so quick to cross the <a href=\"/index.php/Rhoyne\" title=\"Rhoyne\">Rhoyne</a>. <sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Illyrio_Mopatis\" title=\"Illyrio Mopatis\">Illyrio Mopatis</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Khalasar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot64.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_64\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 64\">Chapter 64</a>, Daenerys VIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_52\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 52\">Chapter 52</a>, Daenerys IX.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_5\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 5\">Chapter 5</a>, Tyrion II.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403122927\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.043 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.074 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 344/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8783/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 2211/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 440/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1724/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.020/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 4.51 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   60.707      1 -total\n 65.91%   40.010      1 Template:Italic_title\n 26.28%   15.951      4 Template:Ref\n 16.00%    9.713      4 Template:Ref/core\n 10.60%    6.435      2 Template:Quote\n  4.56%    2.768      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:3813-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403122926 and revision id 270378\n -->\n",
